# Function to automatically filter out the tail end of the violin plot (0.5% for nFeatures, 0.5% for nCounts, and 0.5% for mito)
def filter_genes_counts_mt(anndata): 
    "anndata: AnnData object to filter"
    X = anndata.obs
    nGene_cutOff  = np.quantile(X["n_genes_by_counts"], 0.995).round(-2)
    nCount_cutOff = np.quantile(X["total_counts"], 0.995).round(-2)
    
    # Nuclear capture so mostly no mitochondria so impose a traditional 20% cut off
    mito_cutOff = 20
    mask = (X['n_genes_by_counts'] < nGene_cutOff) & (X['total_counts'] < nCount_cutOff) & (X['pct_counts_mt'] < mito_cutOff)
    print('Filtering cells with nGenes  <', nGene_cutOff)
    print('Filtering cells with nCounts <', nCount_cutOff)
    print('Filtering cells with mitoPct <', mito_cutOff)
    bdata = anndata[mask].copy()
    return bdata
